Ocean
The ocean calls out also,
its waves a roaring hymn,
water rushing towards us,
each drop a fleeting touch,
each crash a reminder
of something vast,
filling memory with salt,
a dance between land and water,
a pulse of life.

Amiri Baraka

- Amiri Baraka
